data.title: High School Reunion Tour: Snoop Dogg and Wiz Khalifa join forces
data.meta_description: Snoop Dogg and Wiz Khalifa will embark on a 33-city tour called High School Reunion Tour, starting on July 7. Warren G, Too $hort and Berner, with special guest DJ Drama, will join the two rappers during the tour.
data.text:
Synopsis

Snoop Dogg and Wiz Khalifa will embark on a 33-city tour called High School Reunion Tour, starting on July 7. Warren G, Too $hort and Berner, with special guest DJ Drama, will join the two rappers during the tour.

Hip-hop icons Snoop Dogg and Wiz Khalifa are teaming up once again for their upcoming High School Reunion Tour. The duo recently released a new collaboration, "Don't Text, Don't Call," and will be joined on tour by Warren G, Too $hort, Berner, and special guest DJ Drama. The 33-city tour will begin on July 7 and will hit various cities across the US, including St. Louis, Atlanta, Brooklyn and Houston.

Snoop and Wiz have been friends since their 2011 hit "Young, Wild, and Free," which peaked at No. 7 on the Billboard Hot 100. They even released a stoner comedy called Mac and Devin Go to High School, which could possibly have a sequel in the works, according to a recent post by Snoop on social media.

In addition to the High School Reunion Tour, Wiz Khalifa will also be embarking on his headlining effort, The Good Trip Tour, which features Joey Bada$$, Smoke DZA, Berner, and Chevy Woods. The seven-date tour will kick off next month.

Tickets for the High School Reunion Tour are already available for Citi card members until March 9 (10 p.m. ET) and will go on general sale on March 10 at 9 am ET on ticketmaster.com. Fans can expect an unforgettable experience from the iconic duo and their all-star lineup of guests.
